<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="91" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="91">
This is the first record of this species for Colombia. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waichert &amp; Fernández &amp; Castro-Huertas &amp; Juanita Rodriguez &amp; Pitts" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1860" class="Hexapoda" family="Pompilidae" genus="Euplaniceps" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euplaniceps notabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notabilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Euplaniceps notabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously recorded from Mexico to Costa Rica (
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, HE" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the American Entomological Society" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" pagination="1 - 442" refId="B7" refString="Evans, HE, 1966. A revision of the Mexican and Central American spider wasps of the subfamily Pompilinae (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Memoirs of the American Entomological Society 20: 1 - 442" title="A revision of the Mexican and Central American spider wasps of the subfamily Pompilinae (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae)." volume="20" year="1966">Evans 1966</bibRefCitation>
). The new combination is proposed based on molecular phylogenetic analyses (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/jbi.12430" author="Rodriguez, J" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Biogeography" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" pagination="495 - 506" refId="B12" refString="Rodriguez, J, von Dohlen, CD, Pitts, JP, 2015. Historical biogeography of the recently diverged widespread spider wasp tribe Aporini (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Journal of Biogeography 42: 495 - 506, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/jbi.12430" title="Historical biogeography of the recently diverged widespread spider wasp tribe Aporini (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/jbi.12430" volume="42" year="2015">Rodriguez et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
), which included 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Pompilidae" genus="Aporus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aporus notabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notabilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Aporus notabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(labeled &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1930" class="Hexapoda" family="Pompilidae" genus="Euplaniceps" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euplaniceps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Euplaniceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.&quot;, voucher PO484) in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1930" class="Hexapoda" family="Pompilidae" genus="Euplaniceps" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euplaniceps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Euplaniceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade, sister to the Antillean 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bradley" authorityYear="1944" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Drepanaporus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Drepanaporus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Drepanaporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species had previously been included in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bradley" authorityYear="1944" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Odontaporus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Odontaporus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Odontaporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bradley, JC" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Entomological Society" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" pagination="23 - 157" refId="B4" refString="Bradley, JC, 1944. A preliminary revision of the Pompilinae (exclusive of the tribe Pompilini) of the Americas (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 70: 23 - 157" title="A preliminary revision of the Pompilinae (exclusive of the tribe Pompilini) of the Americas (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae)." volume="70" year="1944">Bradley (1944)</bibRefCitation>
based on the presence of a tooth in the margin of the inferior mandible and bare eyes. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bradley, JC" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Entomological Society" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" pagination="23 - 157" refId="B4" refString="Bradley, JC, 1944. A preliminary revision of the Pompilinae (exclusive of the tribe Pompilini) of the Americas (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 70: 23 - 157" title="A preliminary revision of the Pompilinae (exclusive of the tribe Pompilini) of the Americas (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae)." volume="70" year="1944">Bradley (1944)</bibRefCitation>
did not mention the presence of this tooth in many 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1930" class="Hexapoda" family="Pompilidae" genus="Euplaniceps" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euplaniceps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Euplaniceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Colomo, de Correa MV" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Lilloana" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" pagination="143 - 165" refId="B6" refString="Colomo, de Correa MV, 1998. Contribucion al conocimiento de los Pompilinae de Argentina (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). V. El genero Euplaniceps Haupt. Acta Zoologica Lilloana 44: 143 - 165" title="Contribucion al conocimiento de los Pompilinae de Argentina (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). V. El genero Euplaniceps Haupt." volume="44" year="1998">Colomo de Correa 1998</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, HE" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the American Entomological Society" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" pagination="1 - 442" refId="B7" refString="Evans, HE, 1966. A revision of the Mexican and Central American spider wasps of the subfamily Pompilinae (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Memoirs of the American Entomological Society 20: 1 - 442" title="A revision of the Mexican and Central American spider wasps of the subfamily Pompilinae (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae)." volume="20" year="1966">Evans (1966)</bibRefCitation>
included this species in 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Pompilidae" genus="Aporus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aporus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Aporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based mainly on the second submarginal cell receiving only one recurrent vein. This character is very variable even within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1930" class="Hexapoda" family="Pompilidae" genus="Euplaniceps" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euplaniceps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Euplaniceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (JR pers. obs.), where the second submarginal cell can receive one or two recurrent veins, with the second recurrent vein sometimes being interstitial with the second intercubital vein. Moreover, females of 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Pompilidae" genus="Aporus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aporus notabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notabilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Aporus notabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do not have a v-shaped spatium frontale as all other 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Pompilidae" genus="Aporus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aporus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Aporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but a flattened area between the antennal alveoli on the same plane as the clypeus which is found in many 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1930" class="Hexapoda" family="Pompilidae" genus="Euplaniceps" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euplaniceps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Euplaniceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Colomo, de Correa MV" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Lilloana" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" pagination="143 - 165" refId="B6" refString="Colomo, de Correa MV, 1998. Contribucion al conocimiento de los Pompilinae de Argentina (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). V. El genero Euplaniceps Haupt. Acta Zoologica Lilloana 44: 143 - 165" title="Contribucion al conocimiento de los Pompilinae de Argentina (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). V. El genero Euplaniceps Haupt." volume="44" year="1998">Colomo de Correa 1998</bibRefCitation>
). Finally, the male genitalia have parameres with parallel-side edges and truncated apex, which is a diagnostic character of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1930" class="Hexapoda" family="Pompilidae" genus="Euplaniceps" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euplaniceps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Euplaniceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males. The two subspecies, 
<taxonomicName authority="notabilis" authorityName="notabilis" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="notabilis" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Hexapoda" family="Pompilidae" genus="Aporus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aporus notabilis subsp. notabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="notabilis" subSpecies="notabilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Aporus notabilis notabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cameron" baseAuthorityYear="1893" class="Hexapoda" family="Pompilidae" genus="Aporus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aporus notabilis subsp. pulchritarsis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="notabilis" subSpecies="pulchritarsis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Aporus notabilis pulchritarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are herein included in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1930" class="Hexapoda" family="Pompilidae" genus="Euplaniceps" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euplaniceps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">Euplaniceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
